																					don&rsquo;t have to be old to get your Succession
																					Planning done!</strong> <br /> <br /> Succession in
																				layman&rsquo;s language means &ldquo;<em>The
																					act or process of following of things in order </em><em>or
																					sequence</em>&rdquo;. In legal parlance it means &ldquo;<em>The
																					sequence in which one person after another succeeds
																					to a title, throne, dignity, or estate</em>&rdquo;.
																				Therefore Succession Planning is about helping a
																				person to pass on their wealth and assets so that it
																				is used for the right purposes by the right people
																				without hassles.<strong></strong><br /> <br />
																				Before proceeding, let me ask you a question - Why
																				are you earning? For whom are you earning? You may
																				feel that you are earning for the bright future of
																				your children, so that your family is secured or so
																				that your children would not have to face the
																				difficulties faced by you. Now how would you like
																				all of this, till you are around or till they are
																				around?<br /> <br /> <strong><img
																					src="{!URLFOR($Resource.images,'images/houseview1img2.jpg ')}"
																					width="300" height="284" hspace="10" align="right" />
																				</strong> There is a reason why at Ffreedom, Succession
																				Planning is placed at the apex of our Financial
																				Planning pyramid. <br /> <br /> All our life we
																				work hard, spend less, save well and invest
																				sensibly. But live in a dream land that
																				&ldquo;nothing will happen to us&rdquo; and decide
																				to wait till old age to decide about distributing
																				wealth. <br /> <br /> Succession planning is
																				almost similar to risk planning. There can be two
																				situations in case of an untimely death of an
																				earning member â€“ either there are assets or there
																				are no assets. If assets are not enough to support
																				the family then life insurance policies help with
																				bridging the gap. But when there are assets whether
																				enough or not, a Will helps in deciding how to use
																				it. <br /> <br /> So, age is not the criteria to
																				pick up the pen and write a Will. Do you have
																				assets, do you have a family and loved ones, do you
																				want to have a say on how the money is to be used
																				during and after your time? If yes to all three
																				questions above, then you should get your Succession
																				Planning done irrespective of your age.<br /> <br />
																				Succession Planning is ignored by most people
																				because of lack of awareness. They do not know that
																				if they do not lawfully keep a track of their wealth
																				or the nomination and pass it on through proper
																				legal documentation; their families could be left
																				high and dry. With the help of our legal team, we
																				advise our members on how to maintain documents,
																				keep a check on nominations, how to pass on wealth
																				during the lifetime which can be with the help of a
																				Power of Attorney or Gift deed or even a trust and
																				how it can be passed on after lifetime with the help
																				of a trust and a Will.<br /> <br /> It is a
																				critical exercise that makes financial planning
																				comprehensive and complete.<br /> <br /> <strong>Neha
